    "title": "Algorithm to Visualize Wildfire-Affected Areas",
    "description": "Visualizes active wildfire occurrences from Sentinel-2 imagery using SWIR-based spectral thresholds blended into a base map that preserves soil, built-up areas, vegetation, and water bodies. Supports three rendering styles: a continuous fire intensity heatmap, and binary fire detection in red or yellow. Includes optional cloud avoidance logic to reduce false detections and burn-scar highlighting via the Normalized Burn Ratio (NBR) for post-fire impact assessment. Adapted from a SentinelHub Custom Script by Markuse, P.",
